=== #32 [HIGH] Keycloak refresh tokens are not revoked on use
## Finding

The tbpro realm has revokeRefreshToken set to false. Refresh tokens remain valid even after being used to obtain new access tokens. A leaked refresh token can be used indefinitely (up to the offline session timeout of 30 days) to obtain new access tokens.

**Severity:** HIGH
**Location:** keycloak/data/import/tbpro-realm.json in [thunderbird/thunderbird-accounts](https://github.com/thunderbird/thunderbird-accounts)

## Remediation

- [ ] Set revokeRefreshToken to true in the Keycloak tbpro realm
- [ ] Test token refresh flows (accounts app, any other OIDC clients) to ensure they handle single-use refresh tokens correctly
