- [ ] Use a customer-managed KMS key with rotation policy
- [ ] Consider MFA Delete for the production bucket

## References

- [Security Posture Review](../docs/thundermail-architecture.md#medium-s3-bucket-hardening-gaps)

=== #22 [MEDIUM] Bootstrap user data script has set -x debug logging
## Finding

The Phase 1 user data script runs with `set -x`, which echoes every command to `/var/log/cloud-init-output.log`. Any environment variables or intermediate values in Phase 1 are logged. User data itself is also accessible via the instance metadata service to any process on the host.

**Severity:** MEDIUM
**Location:** `stalwart_instance_user_data.sh.j2` in [thunderbird/mailstrom](https://github.com/thunderbird/mailstrom)

## Remediation

