- [Security Posture Review](../docs/thundermail-architecture.md#medium-bootstrap-debug-logging)

=== #21 [HIGH] No S3 VPC Gateway Endpoint — blob traffic traverses the internet
## Finding

The VPC has a Secrets Manager interface endpoint but no S3 Gateway Endpoint. All blob storage traffic (email bodies, attachments) leaves the VPC through the NAT gateway and traverses the public internet to reach S3. This adds latency, increases NAT gateway data processing costs, and creates an unnecessary exposure surface.

**Severity:** HIGH
**Location:** `config.prod.yaml` / `__main__.py` in [thunderbird/mailstrom](https://github.com/thunderbird/mailstrom)

## Remediation

- [ ] Add an S3 Gateway Endpoint to the VPC
- [ ] Update route tables for private subnets to route S3 traffic through the endpoint
- [ ] Verify blob storage operations work correctly through the endpoint

## Notes

S3 Gateway Endpoints are free and keep all S3 traffic on the AWS backbone network. This is a zero-risk, high-value change.

