Assess and remediate MZLA's AWS security posture, migrate from per-account IAM users to centralized SSO via AWS IAM Identity Center, and establish foundational security controls across the five-account AWS organization.

## Goals
- **Zero IAM users for humans** — all human access via SSO
- **Zero long-lived access keys for humans** — CLI access via short-lived SSO credentials
- **100% CI/CD on OIDC** — no service account access keys (SES SMTP excepted)
- **Org-wide logging and monitoring** — CloudTrail, GuardDuty, Config in all accounts
- **Baseline SCPs** — guardrails preventing the most common misconfigurations
- **Identity independence** — Keycloak as MZLA's IdP, federated to Identity Center
- **MoCo collaboration** — peer advisory relationship with MoCo security team

## Workstreams

### Assess
- [ ] #3 — AWS Organization Discovery & Security Assessment
- [ ] #9 — Keycloak Discovery & Identity Center Federation (discovery phase)

### Remediate
- [ ] #4 — Quick wins: S3 public access blocks, stale keys, dead IAM users
- [ ] #5 — MFA enforcement for all console users
- [ ] #6 — Deploy org-wide CloudTrail via Pulumi
- [ ] #7 — Deploy baseline SCPs
- [ ] #11 — Enable GuardDuty and Config org-wide
- [ ] #13 — MoCo security collaboration

### Migrate
- [ ] #8 — IAM Identity Center: RFC, configuration, and user onboarding
- [ ] #9 — Keycloak Discovery & Identity Center Federation (federation phase)

### Harden
- [ ] #12 — IAM hardening: disable IAM users, deny creation, break-glass procedure
- [ ] #10 — CI/CD OIDC migration (weeks 4-8, longest tail item)

## Success Metrics
| Metric | Baseline | Target |
|--------|----------|--------|
| Users without MFA | ~13 | 0 |
| Accounts with CloudTrail | 1/5 | 5/5 |
| Accounts with GuardDuty | ? | 5/5 |
| Humans on SSO | 0 | 100% |
| IAM users (humans) | ~22 | 0 |
| CI/CD on OIDC | 1/14 | 14/14 |
| Stale access keys (>90d) | ~10+ | 0 |

## Timeline
- Core security + SSO: ~4 weeks
- CI/CD OIDC migration: weeks 4-8 (repo-by-repo)

