=== #3 AWS Organization Discovery & Security Assessment
## Objective
Run a comprehensive discovery of the MZLA AWS organization to establish a security baseline.

## Scope
- Org structure: accounts, OUs, enabled policy types, service principals
- Per-account IAM audit: users, console access, MFA status, access key age/usage, policies, group memberships
- Per-account security config: CloudTrail, Config, GuardDuty, root MFA, password policy, S3 public access block
- SCP inventory
- IAM Identity Center status
- Cross-account identity correlation (username patterns)
- Service account identification (candidates for OIDC migration)

## Deliverables
- [ ] `discover-mzla-org.py` discovery script (Python/boto3)
- [ ] `mzla-aws-org.yaml` — org structure and per-account inventory
- [ ] `mzla-security-findings.yaml` — findings by severity
- [ ] `mzla-user-access-report.md` — user inventory with effective permissions classification
- [ ] `mzla-security-gap-report.md` — findings, risk matrix, remediation mapping
- [ ] `mzla-group-permset-matrix.md` — permission sets, groups, assignment matrix

## Notes
- Uses cross-account role assumption via `OrganizationAccountAccessRole`
- Access classification: admin / power-user / service-scoped / read-only / minimal / no-access
- Output feeds directly into the Identity Center RFC and migration plan

